com.tractrac.model.lib.api.data

Interface IPosition

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAttachable, IGeoCoordinate, com.tractrac.util.lib.api.serialize.ISerializable, ITimeData
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IPositionSnapped

    public interface IPosition
extends IGeoCoordinate, ITimeData, IAttachable, com.tractrac.util.lib.api.serialize.ISerializable

    A geographical position in latitude-longitude coordinates, recorded at a certain time.

    The position is in the WGS84 coordinate frame.

    TODO: Should it instead return an ICoordinate? That would make it possible to work in geographical coordinates as well as projected coordinates directly, not having to store both.
    Version:
    3.0
    Author:
    Jesper Grooss

      • getDirection

        double getDirection()
        Returns the direction of the carrier at the time of the position. The direction is the 360 degree compass heading, i.e. 0 when the carrier is travelling directly north and 90 when the carrier is travelling directly east.
        Returns:
        the direction of the carrier at the time of the position.
